<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Panteroo:
[B]I am an easy going guy.. and i hate charging the outrageous prices that some spells sell for.

Last night I was in EC hocking some stuff for the weekly peridot resupply. Among some mid level items I was attempting to sell I had 1 level 59 necro spell (Devouring Darkness) and 1 level 60 shaman spell (Torpor).

I get a reply from a necro asking how much I wanted for Devouring Darkness (1600hp DoT + 70% snare). I told him I was not looking for pp but would instead trade it for a level 58+ Cleric spell from the following list:
Naltrons Mark
Blessed Armor of the Risen
Word of Redemption
Marzins Mark
Group Aegolism

Obviously in the market place these spells have a rather wide range of potential value. The necro tried to offer me a variety of other spells in the sub level 55 category. I politely told him that I had no need or use for the other spells and was really only looking to trade Dev. Darkness for the spells I listed. The necro tells me "FINE... I'll give you Naltrons Mark for Devouring Darkness +20kpp". I told him not only did I not have 20kpp to "throw into the deal" but that I had no intention of paying that much extra. I then offered him Dev Darkness +5kpp for Naltrons Mark or he could pick some of my other items in auction + dev darkness for Naltrons Mark... He laughed and called me a stupid n00b. Deal over as far as I was concerned.

For the next 2 hours he sent me /tells trying to buy the spell for pp.... I politely told him that I was using that spell to TRADE for spells I needed, not to make pp. He repeatedly tells me that DevDarkness is not worth nearly as much as Naltrons Mark is (on my server economy he was most likely correct). So i tell him to sell Naltrons Mark to somebody then use the pp to buy Devouring Darkness from somebody else. He complains back to me that he hasn't been able to sell Naltrons Mark for the 25kpp he was asking and that I was the only person he had ever seen auction Devouring Darkness. 

I had something he wanted, he had something I wanted... neither of us had actively sought to get the item we had, but rather had gotten what we had while actively trying to get what the other had acquired. He got his while exp hunting in SF and I got mine while exp hunting in OS. 

He told me I was trying to "sucker" him into a bad deal and how much of a jerk I was. I told him there was no way I was gonna give him a spell AND 20kpp for Naltrons Mark, but if he happened to come across any other spells from my list that he didn't value so highly to go ahead and look me up for a straight trade of spells... if i hadn't traded somebody else for it already.

was I being a greedy jerk to want to trade him a 59necro spell he wanted that I had for a 58cleric spell that I wanted and he had?

I guess I saw it as I was trading my time for his time... my need for his need. With SoV and SoL expansions out its not like lvl55+ kunark spells are falling out of the trees anyway. To add insult to injury, I had on atleast 4 other occassions gone out of my way to go to SF and rez him for free.

/sigh

/rant off[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
